<subSubSection id="AA318DB506C0EEB6561E636189CC6F74" pageId="0" pageNumber="84" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="7DE62AECF6104EDADB0AC6163372C814" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E85253D627B1CAF5DE69C623EEAE5C12" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">
<taxonomicName id="C53D53CFE5BFDBD3206D2E5CD1BBA39C" authorityName="Crespo" authorityYear="2022" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Hogna" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hogna isambertoi" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="isambertoi">
<emphasis id="9A5CDAF764C1B3DD1F5D256E56ED566F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">Hogna isambertoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. can be distinguished from all other Madeiran 
<taxonomicName id="37EA0ADAF625C3530C2148D59B82E3CA" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1885" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Hogna" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hogna" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="588C67BED24BBA14B1BD30F84485E8C2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">Hogna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its genitalia. In males, the embolus is thick and tilted anteriorly at the tip and a tegular apophysis with a very short ventral spur (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B468123D0621DA6AF1E587C85C73E976" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Hogna isambertoi sp. nov. A-C male (SMF): A left male palp, ventral B detail of the median apophysis, anteroventral C SEM image, right male palp, ventral D, E female (SMF): D epigynum, ventral E vulva, dorsal. Abbreviations, male palp: C - cymbium, E - embolus, MA - median apophysis, P - palea, T - tegulum, TA - terminal apophysis. Abbreviations, female genitalia: D - diverticulum, H - epigynal hoods, MS - median septum, S - spermatheca. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A); 0.2 mm (B-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1086.68015.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/646998" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">18A, C</figureCitation>
). In females, the epigynal anterior pockets show convergent lateral borders and the median septum has a wide posterior transverse part (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F3AA93CAF896624D77FA65A7AEC38688" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Hogna isambertoi sp. nov. A-C male (SMF): A left male palp, ventral B detail of the median apophysis, anteroventral C SEM image, right male palp, ventral D, E female (SMF): D epigynum, ventral E vulva, dorsal. Abbreviations, male palp: C - cymbium, E - embolus, MA - median apophysis, P - palea, T - tegulum, TA - terminal apophysis. Abbreviations, female genitalia: D - diverticulum, H - epigynal hoods, MS - median septum, S - spermatheca. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A); 0.2 mm (B-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1086.68015.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/646998" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">18D</figureCitation>
). It is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="D7CF76057825DE85CC6525A82CCBD395" class="Arachnida" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. heeri" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heeri">
<emphasis id="103E3BB44A3FFAE4C2F2CA1A775937F5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">H. heeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="35D6EB45E890D5D874E54A4713E4DEC7" class="Arachnida" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. insularum" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insularum">
<emphasis id="4CC28FCA30744861EE78EF84428A284B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">H. insularum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from which it cannot be somatically differentiated.
</paragraph>
<caption id="42D74B4323886E4B7171CD7C96490182" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1086.68015.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/646998" pageId="0" pageNumber="84" start="Figure 18" startId="F18">
