<figureCitation id="F7B85C7F1B942B8CF76A0A8CE65E4A57" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Hogna isambertoi sp. nov. A-C male (SMF): A left male palp, ventral B detail of the median apophysis, anteroventral C SEM image, right male palp, ventral D, E female (SMF): D epigynum, ventral E vulva, dorsal. Abbreviations, male palp: C - cymbium, E - embolus, MA - median apophysis, P - palea, T - tegulum, TA - terminal apophysis. Abbreviations, female genitalia: D - diverticulum, H - epigynal hoods, MS - median septum, S - spermatheca. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A); 0.2 mm (B-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1086.68015.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/646998" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">18A-C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="DA399D1F230D0A8F81A26676712EB3DE" captionStart="Figure 19" captionStartId="F19" captionText="Figure 19. Hogna isambertoi sp. nov. A male habitus, dorsal (SMF) B female habitus, dorsal (SMF). Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1086.68015.figure19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/646999" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">19A</figureCitation>
). Total length: 7.4; carapace: 4.6 long, 3.2 wide.
</paragraph>
<caption id="2B678CAD6FDCD2883FBF23B0D4F9DEF4" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1086.68015.figure19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/646999" pageId="0" pageNumber="84" start="Figure 19" startId="F19">
<paragraph id="47F78FD301E2B4D981FDAF25F94827D4" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis id="F0A0A759ADD5126AE8D5865EABA816AB" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">Figure 19.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="24BB6746B9F29E6C945A40A4CFEF731A" authorityName="Crespo" authorityYear="2022" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Hogna" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hogna isambertoi" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="isambertoi">
