sp. nov. 
<emphasis id="956C08A18FFD167037171652588237A9" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">A</emphasis>
male habitus, dorsal (SMF) 
<emphasis id="D48095B158E46D1729BF822D3DED6E82" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">B</emphasis>
female habitus, dorsal (SMF). Scale bars: 1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="DCAE05B9D9536A174BE0E1A7AF63AD88" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis id="422212239B653B0644541C22F251456B" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">Colour</emphasis>
: carapace greyish brown, covered with short black setae, with a median yellow longitudinal band, anteriorly broadened, covered with short white setae; two yellow marginal bands, suffused with grey patches, covered with short white setae; four black striae well visible on each flank. Chelicerae yellow, with grey suffused patches, covered in black and white setae. Gnathocoxae and labium overall pale yellow, with posterior margin with suffused grey patch; sternum pale yellow, with V-shaped grey patch. Legs pale yellow, with irregular grey suffused patches, except anterior metatarsi and tarsi, yellowish orange. Pedipalps yellow. Abdomen with a pair of anterolateral black patches, extending laterally into grey to black flanks; a median faint dark lanceolate patch is bordered by two yellowish longitudinal bands interconnected in anterior half, posteriorly by means of dark chevrons; venter yellowish, with large blackish patches near spinnerets and small patches medially.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DAE87A02160AA094E990F31658BCF0E5" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis id="AE5D178ADE2C2E0717BCB9C777DB0565" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">Eyes</emphasis>
: MOQ: MW = 0.8 PW, MW = 1.1 LMP, MW = 1.1 AW; Cl = 0.5 DAME. Anterior eye row slightly procurved.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BC4C1BB8DE7BC300BB78C184F6256638" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis id="8BA570C1979E2B79A6713D5BEE0B2E14" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">Legs</emphasis>
: Measurements: Leg I: 11.7, TiI: 2.6; Leg IV: 13.8, TiIV: 2.8; TiIL/D: 6.6. Spination of Leg I: FeI: d1.1.1, p0.0.1; TiI: p1.0.1, v2l.2l.2s; MtI: p0.0.1, r0.0.1, v2l.2l.1s. MtI with sparse scopulae in basal half and dense scopulae on distal half.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FFD2A7B9FA3656A225663F34C847CABB" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis id="BDC9D7D74179254454A60E650B4CAFDF" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">Pedipalp</emphasis>
: cymbium with one spine along prolateral rim and five dark, stout, macrosetae at tip, Fe with two dorsal and an apical row of four spines. Tegular apophysis with ventral spur very short, blunt, with a concave ridge leading to a thin apical point (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="EE2B8C13A39E02EE67D6A76031E3C33E" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Hogna isambertoi sp. nov. A-C male (SMF): A left male palp, ventral B detail of the median apophysis, anteroventral C SEM image, right male palp, ventral D, E female (SMF): D epigynum, ventral E vulva, dorsal. Abbreviations, male palp: C - cymbium, E - embolus, MA - median apophysis, P - palea, T - tegulum, TA - terminal apophysis. Abbreviations, female genitalia: D - diverticulum, H - epigynal hoods, MS - median septum, S - spermatheca. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A); 0.2 mm (B-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1086.68015.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/646998" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">18A, B</figureCitation>
); terminal apophysis in close apposition with subterminal apophysis, which is blade-shaped with blunt end (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F9F9FA290CDB456F04E2059138D9B02C" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Hogna isambertoi sp. nov. A-C male (SMF): A left male palp, ventral B detail of the median apophysis, anteroventral C SEM image, right male palp, ventral D, E female (SMF): D epigynum, ventral E vulva, dorsal. Abbreviations, male palp: C - cymbium, E - embolus, MA - median apophysis, P - palea, T - tegulum, TA - terminal apophysis. Abbreviations, female genitalia: D - diverticulum, H - epigynal hoods, MS - median septum, S - spermatheca. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A); 0.2 mm (B-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1086.68015.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/646998" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">18A, C</figureCitation>
); embolus long and thick, with tip tilted anteriorly (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="27805AE2397F4B7B001AD96BDF4CF84B" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Hogna isambertoi sp. nov. A-C male (SMF): A left male palp, ventral B detail of the median apophysis, anteroventral C SEM image, right male palp, ventral D, E female (SMF): D epigynum, ventral E vulva, dorsal. Abbreviations, male palp: C - cymbium, E - embolus, MA - median apophysis, P - palea, T - tegulum, TA - terminal apophysis. Abbreviations, female genitalia: D - diverticulum, H - epigynal hoods, MS - median septum, S - spermatheca. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A); 0.2 mm (B-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1086.68015.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/646998" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">18A</figureCitation>
); palea large (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B9E1A2D1C8203FB267953A10313A4650" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Hogna isambertoi sp. nov. A-C male (SMF): A left male palp, ventral B detail of the median apophysis, anteroventral C SEM image, right male palp, ventral D, E female (SMF): D epigynum, ventral E vulva, dorsal. Abbreviations, male palp: C - cymbium, E - embolus, MA - median apophysis, P - palea, T - tegulum, TA - terminal apophysis. Abbreviations, female genitalia: D - diverticulum, H - epigynal hoods, MS - median septum, S - spermatheca. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A); 0.2 mm (B-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1086.68015.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/646998" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">18A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="12F1DAC1CC8843D6AF78BC2A7F2FAFE5" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis id="31213D7E2A4EADDFD4E6B1D1EAE23DE5" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">Female paratype</emphasis>
: (Figs 
<figureCitation id="E680E9D4095CCB8EB3E3A2AE2E881FE1" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Hogna isambertoi sp. nov. A-C male (SMF): A left male palp, ventral B detail of the median apophysis, anteroventral C SEM image, right male palp, ventral D, E female (SMF): D epigynum, ventral E vulva, dorsal. Abbreviations, male palp: C - cymbium, E - embolus, MA - median apophysis, P - palea, T - tegulum, TA - terminal apophysis. Abbreviations, female genitalia: D - diverticulum, H - epigynal hoods, MS - median septum, S - spermatheca. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A); 0.2 mm (B-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1086.68015.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/646998" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">18D, E</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="E8939382586DDD62B8FF09A090F52F64" captionStart="Figure 19" captionStartId="F19" captionText="Figure 19. Hogna isambertoi sp. nov. A male habitus, dorsal (SMF) B female habitus, dorsal (SMF). Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1086.68015.figure19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/646999" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">19B</figureCitation>
). Total length 12.1; carapace: 4.7 long, 3.6 wide.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5CEC6D2A0FCA7AF89FC2E8AD5AEBBCAC" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis id="52B2FC912CB8FC433F516F158C3F5BE5" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">Colour</emphasis>
: overall as in male, but darker in legs, chelicera and prosoma, where additional faint striae are present. Abdomen is lighter, with central chevrons faded, possibly due to pregnancy and correspondent tegument extension.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="62E4A071236B02656AE6E91FB6A8B5C2" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis id="8D7E0BF06CD4E3C30FE2283A500BA2AE" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">Eyes</emphasis>
: MOQ: MW = 0.8 PW, MW = 1.2 LMP, MW = 1.8 AW; Cl = 0.4 DAME. Anterior eye row slightly procurved.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="82127350FF8DEE97EDE566CCA4EBFB7B" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis id="4302FFB37EC9E61D533B40AE3DC906FE" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">Legs</emphasis>
: Measurements: Leg I: 9.9, TiI: 1.7; Leg IV: 13.0, TiIV: 2.6; TiIL/D: 3.2. Spination of Leg I: FeI: d1.1.0, p0.0.1-2; TiI: p0.0.0-1, v2l.2l.2s; MtI: p0.0.1, r0.0.1, v2l.2l.1s. MtI with sparse scopulae in basal half and dense scopulae on distal half.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="931BD91A9B19BEB6E5A17BD4BCD15F03" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis id="89555419133EB59BC3DD2890D7E27312" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">Epigyne</emphasis>
: anterior pockets touching, short, with lateral borders parallel (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="94190949ABA6E68D62986219ACC9A614" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Hogna isambertoi sp. nov. A-C male (SMF): A left male palp, ventral B detail of the median apophysis, anteroventral C SEM image, right male palp, ventral D, E female (SMF): D epigynum, ventral E vulva, dorsal. Abbreviations, male palp: C - cymbium, E - embolus, MA - median apophysis, P - palea, T - tegulum, TA - terminal apophysis. Abbreviations, female genitalia: D - diverticulum, H - epigynal hoods, MS - median septum, S - spermatheca. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A); 0.2 mm (B-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1086.68015.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/646998" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">18D</figureCitation>
); anterior pocket cavities deep; median septum with wide posterior transverse part (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="AA7F25A229AEBBBE24BD69BBEACFC719" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Hogna isambertoi sp. nov. A-C male (SMF): A left male palp, ventral B detail of the median apophysis, anteroventral C SEM image, right male palp, ventral D, E female (SMF): D epigynum, ventral E vulva, dorsal. Abbreviations, male palp: C - cymbium, E - embolus, MA - median apophysis, P - palea, T - tegulum, TA - terminal apophysis. Abbreviations, female genitalia: D - diverticulum, H - epigynal hoods, MS - median septum, S - spermatheca. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A); 0.2 mm (B-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1086.68015.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/646998" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">18D</figureCitation>
); spermathecae oval (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="97AA3BDBA67F014B804E7A36B6FA2AED" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Hogna isambertoi sp. nov. A-C male (SMF): A left male palp, ventral B detail of the median apophysis, anteroventral C SEM image, right male palp, ventral D, E female (SMF): D epigynum, ventral E vulva, dorsal. Abbreviations, male palp: C - cymbium, E - embolus, MA - median apophysis, P - palea, T - tegulum, TA - terminal apophysis. Abbreviations, female genitalia: D - diverticulum, H - epigynal hoods, MS - median septum, S - spermatheca. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A); 0.2 mm (B-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1086.68015.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/646998" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">18E</figureCitation>
); copulatory ducts simple (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="4FEDB0AB05FA7EA6B050FA46371AB6AE" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Hogna isambertoi sp. nov. A-C male (SMF): A left male palp, ventral B detail of the median apophysis, anteroventral C SEM image, right male palp, ventral D, E female (SMF): D epigynum, ventral E vulva, dorsal. Abbreviations, male palp: C - cymbium, E - embolus, MA - median apophysis, P - palea, T - tegulum, TA - terminal apophysis. Abbreviations, female genitalia: D - diverticulum, H - epigynal hoods, MS - median septum, S - spermatheca. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A); 0.2 mm (B-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1086.68015.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/646998" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">18E</figureCitation>
); fertilisation ducts emerging at the base of copulatory duct (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B497B42EB278BEEEC8B3BA3993B5D8E7" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Hogna isambertoi sp. nov. A-C male (SMF): A left male palp, ventral B detail of the median apophysis, anteroventral C SEM image, right male palp, ventral D, E female (SMF): D epigynum, ventral E vulva, dorsal. Abbreviations, male palp: C - cymbium, E - embolus, MA - median apophysis, P - palea, T - tegulum, TA - terminal apophysis. Abbreviations, female genitalia: D - diverticulum, H - epigynal hoods, MS - median septum, S - spermatheca. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A); 0.2 mm (B-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1086.68015.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/646998" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">18E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A349A62334F96AE204D60CCFBC766EDC" pageId="0" pageNumber="84" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="FFDF5796CAE907EA38D6AE07DD6B9417" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9D8575D7BA8615F8A39076551444D9D1" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">the specific epithet is a patronym in honour of Isamberto Silva, who not only collected the only known specimens of this species, but has provided invaluable support during field work.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0FFF59A8852D277287557BD0F6E7D8C8" pageId="0" pageNumber="84" type="intraspecific variation">
<paragraph id="DA490D11FCFC1767DFB20E5586FDEDA0" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">Intraspecific variation.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2402993DB1A7F3C042D4EEC9406434F7" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">Carapace length, males: 4.1-4.3.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1B6095511E6B8A347D5E3CD40A9889A4" pageId="0" pageNumber="84" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="6D907E23816AC827BFBED9D5F7845CE7" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CBB6963A4AF446C544606AE6E454BD7C" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">
This species is known only from the southernmost part of Deserta Grande and Bugio (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="470DEC87A17D6DF92E40B724432CC7C7" captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="F20" captionText="Figure 20. Distribution of H. isambertoi sp. nov. Circles: present records; black triangle: revised record from literature." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1086.68015.figure20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/647000" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">20</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="5EAE2311FCCE51497191A9BE2C3E016A" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1086.68015.figure20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/647000" pageId="0" pageNumber="84" start="Figure 20" startId="F20">
